# BootstrapBlazor UI Conventions

All Blazor UI in `apps/**` MUST be built with the vendored BootstrapBlazor library
(`external/bootstrap-blazor`, referenced via project reference). Reference component
usage and demos at https://www.blazor.zone/introduction.

## Rules

- Prefer BootstrapBlazor components over raw HTML/Bootstrap markup.
- Data lists MUST use `<Table>` with built-in pagination (`IsPagination="true"`,
  `PageItemsSource`) instead of hand-rolled tables/paging.
- Dropdowns MUST use `<Select>` / `<SelectGeneric>` (not raw `<select>` or free-text
  inputs) for fixed option sets (status, role, module, etc.).
- Text/number/password inputs use `BootstrapInput` / `BootstrapInputNumber` /
  `BootstrapPassword`; group content in `<Card>`.
- Modal/dialog forms MUST wrap controls in `<AppFormField Label="...">` with
  `ShowLabel="false"` on inner BootstrapBlazor inputs.
- Money fields use `<AppMoneyInput>` (vi-VN: `.` thousands, `,` decimals).
- Boolean flags use `<Checkbox>`, not `<Switch>`.
- Status enums use `<AppStatusSelect>` with colored badges.
- Large catalog lookups use `<CustomerLookupSelect>` or `Select` with
  `ShowSearch` + `OnQueryAsync` (Select2-style API search).
- The admin shell body MUST be a Chrome-style tab workspace: the `<Layout>` uses
  `UseTabSet="true"` and `TabStyle="TabStyle.Chrome"` so menu clicks open closeable
  Chrome tabs.

## Example

```razor
<Layout UseTabSet="true" TabStyle="TabStyle.Chrome" TabDefaultUrl="/" ...>
    ...
</Layout>

<Select TValue="string" @bind-Value="_status" Items="_statusOptions" DisplayText="Trạng thái" />

<Table TItem="UserDto" OnQueryAsync="OnQueryAsync"
       IsPagination="true" PageItemsSource="_pageItems" ShowSearch="true">
    <TableColumns>
        <TableColumn @bind-Field="@context.UserName" Text="Tên đăng nhập" Sortable="true" />
    </TableColumns>
</Table>
```
